    "explanation": "<p>The correct answer is:</p>\n<p><strong>Option 1: As biomass</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong>  </p>\n<p>The standing crop at a particular trophic level is measured as the <strong>biomass</strong> (the mass of living material) present at that level at a given time. Productivity (gross or net) refers to the rate of production of biomass, while a pyramid of energy represents energy flow, not the standing crop.</p>",
